# Walkthrough - Cookie Consent Banner Implementation

I have implemented a comprehensive cookie consent system for Next Academy, ensuring legal compliance while maintaining premium aesthetics.

## Changes Made

### UI Components

#### [cookie-consent.tsx](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/components/cookie-consent.tsx)
- Created a client-side component for the cookie banner.
- Detects user preference from `localStorage`.
- Supports Arabic and English with automated locale detection.
- Dispatches a custom event `cookie-consent-accepted` for retroactive tracking.

#### [cookie-consent.module.css](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/components/cookie-consent.module.css)
- Implemented a floating glassmorphism banner.
- Uses `backdrop-filter: blur(12px)` for a premium feel.
- Fully RTL compatible with directional spacing.
- Dark theme styling with red accents matching the platform's brand.

#### [source-tracker.tsx](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/components/source-tracker.tsx)
- A utility component that initializes UTM tracking on page changes, respecting the user's consent.

### Core Logic

#### [source-tracking.ts](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/lib/source-tracking.ts)
- Added `initializeSourceTracking()` to persist UTM sources only when consent is granted.
- Implemented retroactive tracking (listens for the consent event to save sources detected earlier in the session).
- Added `getPersistedContactSource()` to safely retrieve stored source data.

### Integration

#### [layout.tsx](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx)
- Mounted the `CookieConsent` and `SourceTracker` components at the root level.

## Verification

### Manual Check
- **Banner Appearance**: Verified that the banner appears for new visitors.
- **Persistence**: Verified that clicking "Accept All" or "Decline" stores the preference in `localStorage`.
- **RTL Support**: Verified that the layout correctly flips for Arabic users.
- **Design**: Confirmed the use of glassmorphism and the correct color/accent tokens.

### Technical Check
- **Type Safety**: The code adheres to strict TypeScript standards.
- **Performance**: Banner is client-side only and uses lightweight CSS Modules.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The source tracking now strictly requires user consent. UTM parameters will not be persisted if the user declines or has not yet interacted with the banner.
